'''''Star Wars'' 9''' is the ninth issue of the [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'']]. It was written by [[Roy Thomas]], illustrated by [[Howard Chaykin]], and first published by [[Marvel Comics]] on [[December 13]], [[1977]]. It features the story "'''Showdown on a Wasteland World!'''," in which the [[Star-Hoppers of Aduba-3]] defend the village [[Onacra]] from the [[Cloud-Riders/Legends|Cloud-Riders]].

==Publisher's summary==
''When the High-hounds attack, a mythical monster is summoned that may mean the end for a village as well as Han and Chewie!''

==Plot summary==
Han Solo, Chewbacca, and the [[Star-Hoppers of Aduba-3]] arrive at [[Ramiz]]'s village [[Onacra]], only to find it under attack by flying [[High-hound]]s. They repel the beasts, saving the life of a young girl named [[Merri Shen Doshun|Merri]], who is the daughter of [[Oncho Shen|Oncho]], the village spokesman. Their relief is short-lived as [[Serji-X Arrogantus]] and his [[Cloud-Riders/Legends|Cloud-Riders]] attack. The Star-Hoppers valiantly defend the village from the attack, but not without cost, as [[FE-9Q]] is destroyed in the fray. However, Merri's grandfather the [[Old One]], a [[Shaman/Legends|shaman]], dismisses the hired [[Spacer/Legends|spacers']] help and summons a large, mythical reptilian monster called the [[Behemoth from the World Below]] to handle the invading Cloud-Riders.

Meanwhile, [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] informs [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] that he has found a new location for the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] base in the [[Drexel system/Legends|Drexel system]]. The transmission suddenly ends, and a worried Leia sets out to find Luke.

==Development==
[[Roy Thomas]] was the writer/editor on this issue. [[Howard Chaykin]] and [[Tom Palmer]] were the illustrators, [[Tom Palmer]] the colorist, [[John Costanza]] the letterer, and [[Archie Goodwin]] the consulting editor on this issue. This issue includes a special pin-up page of Han, Chewbacca, Luke, and Leia drawn by Howard Chaykin.

